A Liverpool FC fan has died after falling ill before kick off last night. The spectator suffered a medical emergency before the Merseyside team were due to play Benfica in the Champions League. A club spokesperson has confirmed the fan died despite the best efforts of paramedics and fans. People rushed to help him inside Anfield but he was pronounced dead after being rushed to hospital. The identity of the deceased has not been confirmed. According to the LiverpoolEcho, the fan took ill around 20 minutes before the match was scheduled to begin. A statement from the club read: ‘It is with great regret that Liverpool Football Club can confirm that a supporter who was taken ill ahead of last night’s fixture against Benfica has sadly passed away. ‘First and foremost, the condolences and the thoughts of everyone at the club are with the supporter’s family, loved ones and friends. ‘We would like to thank the emergency services for their heroic efforts in providing urgent care and our appreciation to our medical professionals, stewards and all supporters in the vicinity of the incident for their assistance.’ Liverpool progressed to the semi-final of the Champions League after beating their Portuguese opponents 3-2 in the second leg. A full capacity 53,000-strong crowd were inside Anfield to watch the crunch tie. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.